Pre-Game Insights: The Egyptian national team, led by Hossam Hassan, is preparing to face Guinea-Bissau at the 24 de September Stadium in the city of Bissau, in the fourth round of the World Cup qualifiers.

The expected formation of the Egyptian national team for the match against Guinea Bissau today, led by Mohamed Salah, is as follows: Goalkeeper: Mohamed El-Shenawy. Defense line: Mohamed Hani - Rami Rabia - Mohamed Abdel Moneim - Mohamed Hamdi. Midfield: Marwan Attia - Ahmed Sayed Zizou - Hamdi Fathi. Offensive line: Mohamed Salah - Mahmoud Hassan Trezeguet - Mustafa Mohamed.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Egypt national team group in the World Cup qualifiers includes: Egypt - Guinea Bissau - Burkina Faso - Sierra Leone - Ethiopia - Djibouti.
The Egyptian national team leads the first group of the 2026 World Cup qualifying groups with 9 points.

The Egyptian team defeated Djibouti (6-0), Sierra Leone (2-0), and Burkina Faso (2-1). Guinea-Bissau comes in second place with 5 points. It won over Djibouti (1-0), tied with Burkina Faso (1-1) and tied with Ethiopia (0-0).
